The paper deals with finding a small spectral approximation for a tall matrix in an online setting, which involves algorithms for machine learning and data analysis. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.DS and cs.LG are the most likely categories as the paper deals with algorithms for data analysis and approximation. cs.IT and cs.NA are also possible categories as the paper involves numerical methods and information theory. Finally, cs.SI is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with social networks, but rather with matrix approximation.
